Here's an example of how you can use Java streams to print integers greater than a given value:

```java
import java.util.stream.IntStream;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int threshold = 5; // Define the threshold value

        // Use IntStream to generate a stream of integers
        IntStream stream = IntStream.range(1, 11); // Generate integers from 1 to 10

        // Use the filter method to filter out integers less than or equal to the threshold
        stream.filter(i -> i > threshold)
              .forEach(System.out::println); // Print the filtered integers

        // Alternatively, you can use the boxed method to convert the IntStream to a Stream of Integers
        stream.boxed().filter(i -> (int)i > threshold)
                      .forEach(System.out::println);
    }
}
```

In this example, we first define the threshold value as 5. We then use `IntStream.range(1, 11)` to generate a stream of integers from 1 to 10. We use the `filter` method to filter out integers less than or equal to the threshold, and then use `forEach` to print the filtered integers.

